<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="184" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1166,1553]" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">
In the protologue, the specimens on which this name is based are not specifically indicated, but the herbarium of Munich (M) and the Herbarium Zuccarini are repositories of Martius collections (
<bibRefCitation author="Martius, C. F. P. V." box="[1080,1238,1202,1228]" pageId="4" pageNumber="184" pagination="98 - 102" refId="ref7849" refString="Martius, C. F. P. V. (1826) XXXII Luhea Willd. Nova genera et species plantarum: quas in itinere per Brasiliam MDCCCXVII-MDCCCXX 1 (4): 98 - 102." type="journal article" year="1826">Martius 1826</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S." pageId="4" pageNumber="184" refId="ref8497" refString="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S. (1976 - 1988) Taxonomic Literature: A selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types, 2 nd ed., Smithsonian Libraries, last updated 28 Jun. 2012. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 48631" type="book" year="1976">Stafleu &amp; Cowan 1976</bibRefCitation>
–1988: 325). The typification claim by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cunha, M. C. S." box="[623,776,1238,1265]" pageId="4" pageNumber="184" pagination="5 - 41" refId="ref7419" refString="Cunha, M. C. S. (1985) Revisao das especies do genero Luehea Willd. (Tiliaceae), ocorrentes no estado do Rio de Janeiro. Sellowia, Anais Botanicos do Herbario Barbosa Rodrigues 37: 5 - 41." type="journal article" year="1985">
<collectingCountry box="[623,696,1238,1264]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">Cunha</collectingCountry>
(1985)
</bibRefCitation>
to be the 
<typeStatus box="[880,978,1238,1264]" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">holotype</typeStatus>
is corrected here as lectotypification (firststep typification) according to the Art. 9.10 of the ICN. We have found 
<typeStatus box="[924,1105,1274,1300]" isOtherTypeStatus="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">other specimens</typeStatus>
from the collection of Martius, both in M and other herbaria, with different numbers (
<emphasis box="[762,804,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">263</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[820,862,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">265</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[878,978,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">269, 609</emphasis>
) or 
<emphasis box="[1029,1068,1311,1336]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">s.n.</emphasis>
, and almost all without indicated locations. Since only location, but no collection number, is noted in the protologue, we accepted only the specimens 
<emphasis box="[136,273,1383,1408]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">Martius s.n.</emphasis>
as the original material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1826" box="[590,742,1382,1408]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paniculata">
<emphasis box="[590,742,1382,1408]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">L. paniculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because they are the only specimens with the location noted. Therefore, in accordance with Arts. 9.3 and 9.4 of the ICN, we designate herein 
<emphasis box="[1027,1161,1419,1444]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">Martius s.n.</emphasis>
(M0210164) as a secondstep 
<typeStatus box="[192,298,1454,1480]" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">lectotype</typeStatus>
, in addition to being the best-preserved specimen and congruent with the protologue’s description. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:039287B9FFDDFFA0FF43FB90FAD4F9E0:8EE46074FFDDFFA0FF43FA43FF7FFA1D" box="[136,180,1490,1516]" country="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" county="Based" municipality="Figure" name="The" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">The</location>
specimen M0210162 is only a reproduction of 
<collectingMunicipality box="[725,798,1490,1516]" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">Figure</collectingMunicipality>
62 from Martius` work. 
<collectingCounty box="[1085,1153,1490,1516]" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">Based</collectingCounty>
on the type materials, the application of the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1826" box="[407,556,1526,1552]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="4" pageNumber="184" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="paniculata">
<emphasis box="[407,556,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">L. paniculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confirmed as an accepted species, as proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cunha, M. C. S." box="[1149,1222,1526,1552]" pageId="4" pageNumber="184" pagination="5 - 41" refId="ref7419" refString="Cunha, M. C. S. (1985) Revisao das especies do genero Luehea Willd. (Tiliaceae), ocorrentes no estado do Rio de Janeiro. Sellowia, Anais Botanicos do Herbario Barbosa Rodrigues 37: 5 - 41." type="journal article" year="1985">
<collectingCountry box="[1149,1222,1526,1552]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="4" pageNumber="184">Cunha</collectingCountry>
</bibRefCitation>
(1985).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
